narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Halsey and Molly are great, there were difficulties with communication with admin about the exhibition

This class is normally handled by the DUS; this semester due to the transition to a new DUS the course was co-taught by Halsey Rodman and Molly Zuckerman-Hartung. I quite enjoyed my discussions with Molly, but Halsey's direction for the course did not seem to be reflective of what I thought the course should be geared toward. It's hard to be critical or offer feedback knowing that in the future this class will be taught differently and by a different person.

Strengths: 
- Profs were cool and kind! 

Weaknesses: 
- It was super late
- I didn't do much in the class that aided my thesis
